# Per-instance runtime state written by the dev server / production daemon.
# `runtime.json` is the only tracked file (the deploy-time overrides for
# webuiPort, hookAutoLoad, etc); everything else here is operator-private:
#   * webui.json          — admin password hash + rotation state
#   * consent.json        — EULA/PRIVACY acceptance per agreement version
#   * notifications.json  — per-account webhook destinations
#   * onebot_<uin>.json   — per-uin OneBot transport binding (HTTP/WS ports etc)
#   * ui.json             — WebUI panel layout per operator
#
# Without this ignore file, every `pnpm dev:mode` / `node dist/index.mjs`
# leaves a 5-file untracked surface in `packages/core/config/` that pollutes
# `git status` and would accidentally commit local creds if `git add -A` is used.

*
!.gitignore
!runtime.json
